The paper focuses on using NLP-based techniques for identifying and extracting highlights from video data, which is a common problem in the market research industry. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) or Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates multiple classes of models, including gradient boosting and recurrent neural networks, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning applications. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision (cs.CV), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Overall, cs.CL and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI.
